{
  "texts": [
    "DTSyn (Hu et al. 2022) extracts drug features using cell line data and known train's data labels.",
    "However, it's less accurate than other machine learning models for predicting drug synergy scores of drugs that it has not seen so far.",
    "MOOMIN's model (Rozemberczki et al. 2022) lacks a defined threshold for categorizing drug synergism.",
    "It employs random walk on a drug-target network and GCN to embed drugs and capture structural features.",
    "However, its performance is comparatively weaker due to the absence of cell line features and comprehensive drug-related information, unlike other GCN-based models."
  ]
}